    "Metadata": {
        "Id": "b4039382-c590-4b51-b25e-830a9a73e983",
        "Type": "usercreated",
        "Title": "Hungarian Fairytales",
        "Location": "LOCATION_ELEGANT_LLAMA",
        "PublicId": "131849828810",
        "ScenePath": "assembly:/_pro/scenes/missions/elegant/scene_llama.entity",
        "TileImage": "$($repository 08428eba-b2f2-40f2-86c8-8157a8706426).Image",
        "Description": "Listen, Malevolent One! I&apos;m going to tell you a hungarian fairytale about deception, tragedy, and death:\rThe prince of the land once had two boys. He didn&apos;t know about them yet, so the witch has switched them out for 2 of her dogs. After thinking that his boys were in fact pups, the prince became furious and brought wrath upon the closest ones to him. He soon found out about the witch&apos;s scheme, so he made sure she was severely punished...\r\rThis is exactly what you will have to do, &quot;prince&quot;!",
